1
00:00:08,529 --> 00:00:10,156
[somber music playing]

2
00:00:11,115 --> 00:00:12,116
[sighs]

3
00:00:30,634 --> 00:00:32,011
[shudders]

4
00:00:35,014 --> 00:00:37,183
-[monitor beeping]
-[respirator hissing]

5
00:00:44,607 --> 00:00:47,443
[suctioning]

6
00:00:51,489 --> 00:00:52,490
[panting] Ha-gyeong.

7
00:00:53,449 --> 00:00:54,283
Min-beom.

8
00:00:54,366 --> 00:00:55,618
Where's Gang-yong?

9
00:00:55,701 --> 00:00:58,954
His brain has a hemorrhage.
He's having surgery now.

10
00:01:01,373 --> 00:01:03,584
MIN GANG-YONG: PROCEDURE IN PROGRESS

11
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:07,922
[whimpering]

12
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:13,135
[crying]

13
00:01:14,595 --> 00:01:15,596
Oh.

14
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:17,348
Woo-jin, what's wrong?

15
00:01:18,474 --> 00:01:19,809
K… Kang In-beom has…

16
00:01:19,892 --> 00:01:20,726
Yeah?

17
00:01:21,227 --> 00:01:22,561
[cries]

18
00:01:22,645 --> 00:01:24,230
He took Mom. He has her.

19
00:01:24,814 --> 00:01:25,731
What?

20
00:01:25,815 --> 00:01:27,691
-I'm so sorry.
-[Gun-woo] Oh.

21
00:01:28,359 --> 00:01:31,112
-[Gun-woo sighs]
-[Woo-jin sobbing]

22
00:01:31,195 --> 00:01:33,489
[Woo-jin] I tried,
but I couldn't protect her.

23
00:01:34,073 --> 00:01:35,032
I don't…

24
00:01:36,033 --> 00:01:37,743
I should just die.

25
00:01:37,827 --> 00:01:42,206
No, no. Woo-jin, no. It's okay.
You tried. It's not your fault.

26
00:01:44,041 --> 00:01:46,293
Oh, Mom!

27
00:01:46,836 --> 00:01:49,380
-[breathes heavily]
-[Woo-jin sobs]

28
00:01:49,463 --> 00:01:51,006
GWANG-MU: THE BOYS ARE IN TROUBLE

29
00:01:51,090 --> 00:01:52,133
I COULDN'T PROTECT THEM

30
00:02:08,899 --> 00:02:10,901
[tense music playing]

31
00:02:19,827 --> 00:02:21,829
[tense electronic music playing]

32
00:02:46,812 --> 00:02:49,398
BLOODHOUNDS 2

33
00:02:49,481 --> 00:02:50,399
[music stops]

34
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:51,775
[knocking on door]

35
00:02:54,737 --> 00:02:55,571
[man] Enter.

36
00:02:55,654 --> 00:02:58,282
DIRECTOR OF INVESTIGATIONS

37
00:02:59,783 --> 00:03:01,243
[somber music playing]

38
00:03:01,327 --> 00:03:03,996
We need to move Yun Tae-geom's
family to a safe house.

39
00:03:04,580 --> 00:03:06,248
Isn't Im Baek-jeong wanted?

40
00:03:06,832 --> 00:03:08,959
He won't have time for revenge
if he's busy running.

41
00:03:09,585 --> 00:03:11,754
Im Baek-jeong will never stop,
even if he's running,

42
00:03:11,837 --> 00:03:13,422
Enough. That's too much.

43
00:03:13,505 --> 00:03:15,216
In what world is it too much?

44
00:03:15,299 --> 00:03:18,135
Yun Tae-geom was murdered
while helping the police.

45
00:03:18,219 --> 00:03:19,345
He was working with us.

46
00:03:19,428 --> 00:03:22,264
Isn't it our duty
to ensure that his family will be safe?

47
00:03:22,348 --> 00:03:24,391
They can hire private security.

48
00:03:24,475 --> 00:03:27,102
Who will take responsibility
if that team fails?

49
00:03:27,186 --> 00:03:29,021
That security team will.

50
00:03:29,605 --> 00:03:31,232
That's why they'll handle it.

51
00:03:31,732 --> 00:03:32,566
[gasps]

52
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:35,402
Don't cause any trouble
and protect a criminal's family.

53
00:03:35,486 --> 00:03:37,363
Instead, try to get the bastard.

54
00:03:38,197 --> 00:03:39,031
[gasps]

55
00:03:39,114 --> 00:03:41,825
If security's so important to you,
figure it out yourself.

56
00:03:48,123 --> 00:03:50,251
We need to eat. Woo-jin?

57
00:03:50,334 --> 00:03:52,878
[tender music playing]

58
00:03:57,174 --> 00:04:00,219
Have a couple of bites.
Eat a bit to take your medicine.

59
00:04:02,137 --> 00:04:02,972
[Gun-woo sighs]

60
00:04:04,223 --> 00:04:05,224
[cell phone buzzing]

61
00:04:05,307 --> 00:04:06,350
LEE WOO-JEONG

62
00:04:07,768 --> 00:04:08,936
Excuse me.

63
00:04:16,443 --> 00:04:17,861
Yes, Woo-jeong?

64
00:04:18,570 --> 00:04:20,281
[Woo-jeong] Gun-woo,
is everything all right?

65
00:04:21,407 --> 00:04:22,366
Yes.

66
00:04:22,950 --> 00:04:26,954
[Woo-jeong] I was told Mr. Min
came out of surgery and he's in the ICU.

67
00:04:27,037 --> 00:04:31,458
His condition's stable,
but we'll need to wait and see.

68
00:04:32,084 --> 00:04:34,003
We're trying to find
your mother's location.

69
00:04:34,086 --> 00:04:37,423
Since it's an area without CCTVs,
we're having difficulties.

70
00:04:37,506 --> 00:04:39,133
I'll keep you updated about it.

71
00:04:39,717 --> 00:04:40,968
Thanks for letting me know.

72
00:04:42,219 --> 00:04:43,470
And how's Mr. Moon doing?

73
00:04:43,971 --> 00:04:46,640
[Woo-jeong] He's awake now.
You should give him a call.

74
00:04:48,559 --> 00:04:49,476
Okay.

75
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,228
[Woo-jeong] Gun-woo,

76
00:04:51,937 --> 00:04:54,565
do you know where you might want to stay
after you're discharged?

77
00:04:56,442 --> 00:04:57,943
I haven't thought about it yet.

78
00:04:58,485 --> 00:05:00,237
Could Yun Tae-geom's family stay with you?

79
00:05:00,321 --> 00:05:03,782
If you're planning on being home?
Just his mom and young daughter?

80
00:05:05,534 --> 00:05:07,077
Yes. I have a spare room there.

81
00:05:07,578 --> 00:05:11,915
Im Baek-jeong killed him
once he found out he also helped us.

82
00:05:11,999 --> 00:05:14,626
Im Baek-jeong might try
murdering Tae-geom's family.

83
00:05:14,710 --> 00:05:17,087
I think it's only right
if we protect them.

84
00:05:17,588 --> 00:05:21,592
We don't have any resources available
so I can only protect them myself now.

85
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,888
It's okay. They're welcome to stay.

86
00:05:25,971 --> 00:05:26,930
[music fades]

87
00:05:29,892 --> 00:05:32,019
[Sin-hyeong] Our employees
work with Special Forces

88
00:05:32,102 --> 00:05:34,021
for their anti-terrorism exercises.

89
00:05:34,104 --> 00:05:37,024
That must be when Lee Dong-hyeon
first met Yun Tae-geom.

90
00:05:37,775 --> 00:05:39,943
Yun Tae-geom introduced him
to Im Baek-jeong later on.

91
00:05:40,611 --> 00:05:41,779
Can you locate him?

92
00:05:41,862 --> 00:05:43,906
Lee Dong-hyeon was a black ops agent.

93
00:05:43,989 --> 00:05:46,200
He's an expert at hiding
so he can't be found.

94
00:05:47,034 --> 00:05:50,287
He might be getting ready to go overseas,
because he's wanted.

95
00:05:50,371 --> 00:05:51,663
We won't let him.

96
00:05:52,247 --> 00:05:54,708
I'll give you the support you need
to stop him from running off.

97
00:05:55,209 --> 00:05:58,295
[ominous music plays]

98
00:05:59,088 --> 00:06:04,635
Im Baek-jeong has made a lot of money
from illegal boxing online.

99
00:06:08,472 --> 00:06:09,640
I have an offer.

100
00:06:10,140 --> 00:06:12,976
We could work together and help society.

101
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:14,228
[tense music playing]

102
00:06:14,311 --> 00:06:17,856
We'll set up a match so Im Baek-jeong
will gamble everything he has in one go.

103
00:06:20,651 --> 00:06:21,610
How?

104
00:06:21,693 --> 00:06:23,904
We'll offer him
another round with Gun-woo.

105
00:06:24,780 --> 00:06:26,073
You'll put in 100 billion won.

106
00:06:26,156 --> 00:06:29,743
Im Baek-jeong will put down
100 billion won too.

107
00:06:29,827 --> 00:06:31,620
And the winner will take it all.

108
00:06:34,206 --> 00:06:35,624
You think he'll go for this?

109
00:06:36,834 --> 00:06:38,836
If he thinks he can win everything.

110
00:06:44,675 --> 00:06:47,010
If it's something he wants,
he'll be there.

111
00:06:47,094 --> 00:06:49,263
He's not the type to be scared easily.

112
00:06:50,013 --> 00:06:51,390
And since he has a hostage,

113
00:06:51,473 --> 00:06:53,767
he will believe
that he has a shield from the police.

114
00:06:57,729 --> 00:06:58,730
[music fades]

115
00:07:00,023 --> 00:07:02,025
[Mr. Moon] I fractured my collarbone.

116
00:07:02,526 --> 00:07:04,236
And my cheekbone

117
00:07:04,736 --> 00:07:07,072
is caved in, according to the doctors.

118
00:07:07,573 --> 00:07:11,743
[sighs] I feel really bad.
I should've been there with you guys too.

119
00:07:12,494 --> 00:07:13,745
Gun-woo,

120
00:07:14,663 --> 00:07:16,039
you're not Superman.

121
00:07:16,123 --> 00:07:17,749
No one is.

122
00:07:18,876 --> 00:07:21,545
Just be a good friend to Woo-jin, Gun-woo.

123
00:07:23,505 --> 00:07:25,716
[poignant music playing]

124
00:07:28,719 --> 00:07:30,137
Just remember that

125
00:07:31,013 --> 00:07:32,431
no one's always a hero.

126
00:07:33,891 --> 00:07:35,017
Okay.

127
00:07:35,976 --> 00:07:38,353
That's good. What are you gonna do?

128
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,898
I'll go back to the house tomorrow.

129
00:07:41,732 --> 00:07:43,275
I contacted a friend.

130
00:07:44,318 --> 00:07:46,820
He's gonna help you out
while I recover here.

131
00:07:48,071 --> 00:07:49,031
Who is it?

132
00:07:49,698 --> 00:07:51,909
When you see him, you'll know who it is.

133
00:07:53,285 --> 00:07:54,369
Thanks.

134
00:08:22,689 --> 00:08:23,815
Let's go.

135
00:08:31,198 --> 00:08:32,282
[Gun-woo sighs]

136
00:08:41,959 --> 00:08:43,001
[music fades]

137
00:08:46,797 --> 00:08:48,757
-[doorbell chimes]
-[vacuum stops]

138
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:50,842
[gentle music playing]

139
00:08:58,976 --> 00:09:00,394
-[Woo-jeong] Gun-woo.
-Hello.

140
00:09:01,103 --> 00:09:02,396
Okay, let's go inside.

141
00:09:02,896 --> 00:09:04,106
Please, watch your step.

142
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:09,570
Hello.

143
00:09:10,612 --> 00:09:12,447
I know you!

144
00:09:25,961 --> 00:09:27,379
Min-a.

145
00:09:30,257 --> 00:09:31,341
It's you.

146
00:09:31,925 --> 00:09:32,759
You're okay?

147
00:09:33,343 --> 00:09:34,303
Yeah.

148
00:09:35,137 --> 00:09:36,430
Do you like stickers?

149
00:09:37,431 --> 00:09:39,016
[chuckles softly] Yeah.

150
00:09:39,683 --> 00:09:40,767
Let's do it.

151
00:09:40,851 --> 00:09:41,810
[music fades]

152
00:09:48,817 --> 00:09:52,904
His intracranial pressure was high from
the injury he sustained in the explosion.

153
00:09:53,614 --> 00:09:55,574
They'll have to wait until he wakes up.

154
00:09:56,074 --> 00:09:59,828
He's not in any condition to move, and it
might take time for him to fully recover.

155
00:09:59,911 --> 00:10:01,913
[somber music playing]

156
00:10:03,498 --> 00:10:04,541
From now on,

157
00:10:05,250 --> 00:10:07,127
we'll do things on our own.

158
00:10:09,504 --> 00:10:11,840
I've thought about ways
we might rescue your mother.

159
00:10:11,923 --> 00:10:14,301
[tense music playing]

160
00:10:15,886 --> 00:10:18,472
And how we can stop Im Baek-jeong
from fleeing Korea.

161
00:10:19,056 --> 00:10:21,391
My uncle's the director
of the National Intelligence Service.

162
00:10:21,475 --> 00:10:22,392
He's willing to help.

163
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:27,522
Gun-woo, this won't be easy.

164
00:10:28,982 --> 00:10:30,942
Could you fight Im Baek-jeong again?

165
00:10:36,698 --> 00:10:38,492
It can draw him out of hiding.

166
00:10:42,454 --> 00:10:45,540
But if he knows he's wanted,
would he show up?

167
00:10:45,624 --> 00:10:47,501
He won't care if he gets caught.

168
00:10:47,584 --> 00:10:50,379
And if the cops arrive,
he'll threaten to hurt Ms. Yoon.

169
00:10:50,962 --> 00:10:51,922
But he won't.

170
00:10:53,256 --> 00:10:55,133
I'll offer 100 billion won.

171
00:10:57,094 --> 00:10:58,887
Im Baek-jeong will do this.

172
00:11:06,645 --> 00:11:07,938
Yes. I'll do what it takes.

173
00:11:09,564 --> 00:11:10,816
[chuckles softly]

174
00:11:10,899 --> 00:11:12,484
[somber music playing]

175
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:16,530
[sighs]

176
00:11:17,989 --> 00:11:18,990
[music fades]

177
00:11:19,074 --> 00:11:20,909
-[Min-a giggles]
-[Woo-jeong] It's your bedtime.

178
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:29,501
[tense music playing]

179
00:11:48,854 --> 00:11:50,605
[Woo-jeong] This one's yours. [laughs]

180
00:11:50,689 --> 00:11:52,357
Gun-woo, someone's here.

181
00:11:53,191 --> 00:11:54,025
He's outside.

182
00:11:54,985 --> 00:11:57,279
[Min-a giggles]

183
00:12:21,178 --> 00:12:22,095
[sighs]

184
00:12:24,389 --> 00:12:26,183
[Gun-woo cries]

185
00:12:27,142 --> 00:12:28,560
I've missed you guys.

186
00:12:28,643 --> 00:12:30,812
[sobs]

187
00:12:32,355 --> 00:12:34,149
I lost the courage to show up here.

188
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:35,734
Du-yeong.

189
00:12:37,569 --> 00:12:38,570
I'm sorry.

190
00:12:41,364 --> 00:12:43,283
-[Woo-jin] Du-yeong!
-[cries]

191
00:12:44,826 --> 00:12:46,036
[cries] Du-yeong.

192
00:12:49,414 --> 00:12:51,041
[all cry]

193
00:12:54,503 --> 00:12:56,463
Why are you crying like that?

194
00:12:56,546 --> 00:12:58,632
[crying continues]

195
00:12:58,715 --> 00:12:59,591
[Woo-jin] Du-yeong.

196
00:13:03,762 --> 00:13:04,763
[music fades]

197
00:13:05,597 --> 00:13:07,599
He's a big guy with a lot of scars.

198
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:10,519
You can see them over his face.

199
00:13:10,602 --> 00:13:12,604
[somber music playing]

200
00:13:13,688 --> 00:13:14,648
Then,

201
00:13:16,358 --> 00:13:17,943
Kang In-beom showed up.

202
00:13:19,903 --> 00:13:22,155
He's the one who kept hitting me again.

203
00:13:23,323 --> 00:13:25,367
So Ms. Yoon came out of her room.

204
00:13:27,577 --> 00:13:30,455
[cries]

205
00:13:30,539 --> 00:13:32,332
She told him to quit hitting me.

206
00:13:35,544 --> 00:13:37,504
[sniffs] And Ms. Yoon…

207
00:13:39,798 --> 00:13:41,383
said she'd go instead.

208
00:13:45,053 --> 00:13:45,887
I…

209
00:13:48,348 --> 00:13:51,393
was supposed to protect her.

210
00:13:53,395 --> 00:13:54,896
It was my duty.

211
00:13:56,356 --> 00:14:00,402
[sniffs] I hate myself. I do.

212
00:14:14,249 --> 00:14:15,208
[sniffs]

213
00:14:16,167 --> 00:14:17,043
[Du-yeong] I also

214
00:14:18,044 --> 00:14:19,921
can't ever forgive myself…

215
00:14:22,841 --> 00:14:24,009
for what I've done.

216
00:14:25,844 --> 00:14:27,554
I'll never forgive myself.

217
00:14:29,723 --> 00:14:30,849
It's all my fault.

218
00:14:31,975 --> 00:14:36,062
Yang-jung and Mr. Choi died.
I caused that.

219
00:14:37,397 --> 00:14:41,067
[cries]

220
00:14:42,027 --> 00:14:45,572
But you have a chance.
There's still time to save her.

221
00:14:47,699 --> 00:14:49,200
So keep being strong.

222
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,369
I'll help you.

223
00:14:52,287 --> 00:14:53,496
We can do it.

224
00:14:54,956 --> 00:14:55,999
We'll rescue her.

225
00:15:05,884 --> 00:15:06,927
[music fades]

226
00:15:07,010 --> 00:15:08,011
Yes.

227
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:13,850
Guys, look at this.

228
00:15:13,934 --> 00:15:16,686
BLOODHOUNDS: SEOUL
200 MILLION WON IF YOU SAVE MY COLLEAGUES

229
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:17,729
[sniffs]

230
00:15:18,772 --> 00:15:19,773
What is this?

231
00:15:19,856 --> 00:15:20,899
[somber music playing]

232
00:15:20,982 --> 00:15:22,692
For the last four years…

233
00:15:25,612 --> 00:15:26,821
to make ends meet,

234
00:15:28,782 --> 00:15:30,075
I did things I'm not proud of.

235
00:15:35,121 --> 00:15:36,206
I committed murder.

236
00:15:37,874 --> 00:15:39,042
I killed good people,

237
00:15:39,542 --> 00:15:42,003
and bad ones, many, for hire.

238
00:15:43,755 --> 00:15:44,673
I…

239
00:15:47,717 --> 00:15:48,718
became…

240
00:15:52,514 --> 00:15:53,723
a bloodhound.

241
00:16:01,481 --> 00:16:04,859
This chat is
how contract killers find jobs.

242
00:16:05,443 --> 00:16:10,615
It's all anonymous and it's run by a host,
but I've never met him.

243
00:16:12,325 --> 00:16:13,994
The host posts the job listing

244
00:16:14,995 --> 00:16:16,371
and someone accepts it.

245
00:16:16,871 --> 00:16:18,623
We get paid by Bitcoin.

246
00:16:19,124 --> 00:16:22,502
The other day,
the host offered something different.

247
00:16:23,003 --> 00:16:27,424
He said he'll pay whoever rescues
his coworkers, the ones who were arrested.

248
00:16:27,507 --> 00:16:30,510
[inhales sharply] Is that Im Baek-jeong?

249
00:16:35,557 --> 00:16:36,474
Du-yeong,

250
00:16:38,143 --> 00:16:40,979
could you talk to the police officer
we worked with who's downstairs?

251
00:16:41,563 --> 00:16:42,522
A policeman?

252
00:16:42,605 --> 00:16:43,440
[music stops]

253
00:16:43,523 --> 00:16:45,483
We can talk and figure this out together.

254
00:16:46,985 --> 00:16:47,902
Du-yeong,

255
00:16:49,154 --> 00:16:50,447
he's been helping us.

256
00:16:50,947 --> 00:16:51,948
[exhales]

257
00:16:56,244 --> 00:16:59,706
Do you know when the bloodhounds chat
first started by any chance?

258
00:16:59,789 --> 00:17:01,291
I don't know for sure.

259
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:02,876
I, uh…

260
00:17:03,752 --> 00:17:05,086
I joined four years ago.

261
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:09,466
A man who pretended to be a veterinarian,
Moon Dong-jo, is someone we arrested.

262
00:17:09,549 --> 00:17:12,844
He's been involved in many crimes,
including drug manufacturing.

263
00:17:12,927 --> 00:17:14,137
Have you heard of him?

264
00:17:14,804 --> 00:17:17,766
Yes. I've heard his name often.

265
00:17:17,849 --> 00:17:20,727
The host said,
if you get hurt, to go to him.

266
00:17:21,227 --> 00:17:23,521
That's the vet you go to see to treat you.

267
00:17:25,356 --> 00:17:26,483
Where is he now?

268
00:17:27,901 --> 00:17:29,152
Was he arrested?

269
00:17:30,862 --> 00:17:33,823
He was released
once his arrest was denied.

270
00:17:33,907 --> 00:17:35,533
He might be at his house.

271
00:17:35,617 --> 00:17:38,078
If you can say where his home is,

272
00:17:39,662 --> 00:17:41,748
I'll go see him very covertly.

273
00:17:45,418 --> 00:17:46,503
Woo-jeong,

274
00:17:48,254 --> 00:17:49,798
trust him, he's with us.

275
00:18:04,854 --> 00:18:06,272
Du-yeong, we'll join you.

276
00:18:06,773 --> 00:18:08,358
-Gun-woo.
-Yes?

277
00:18:08,441 --> 00:18:12,028
The blood won't show up on my hands.

278
00:18:12,987 --> 00:18:14,614
-Even still.
-Don't worry.

279
00:18:16,074 --> 00:18:17,534
I need to do this for you.

280
00:18:17,617 --> 00:18:19,452
[suspenseful music playing]

281
00:18:19,536 --> 00:18:23,081
But, Du-yeong, he could have others there.

282
00:18:30,630 --> 00:18:31,798
[music intensifies]

283
00:18:39,514 --> 00:18:40,348
It's okay.

284
00:18:50,650 --> 00:18:51,818
[snores]

285
00:19:04,622 --> 00:19:06,416
-[loud crack]
-[Dong-jo groans]

286
00:19:06,499 --> 00:19:08,001
-[music fades]
-[water running]

287
00:19:29,397 --> 00:19:30,273
[Du-yeong exhales]

288
00:19:36,321 --> 00:19:38,239
[tense music playing]

289
00:19:38,323 --> 00:19:41,534
I hate people
that open their mouths and say nothing.

290
00:19:42,035 --> 00:19:44,078
It'd be better
if they don't bother at all.

291
00:19:45,663 --> 00:19:48,541
So when you're ready
to tell me everything,

292
00:19:49,709 --> 00:19:50,877
nod your head.

293
00:19:52,212 --> 00:19:54,172
If you start talking, then stop…

294
00:19:56,216 --> 00:19:57,800
I'll cut off your tongue.

295
00:19:59,052 --> 00:20:03,014
[laughs]

296
00:20:06,559 --> 00:20:07,644
[gasps]

297
00:20:08,770 --> 00:20:13,149
-[slicing]
-[muffled moaning]

298
00:20:14,442 --> 00:20:18,529
[muffled shrieking]

299
00:20:18,613 --> 00:20:21,074
[whimpering]

300
00:20:21,157 --> 00:20:22,075
[muffled pleading]

301
00:20:22,158 --> 00:20:23,993
[muffled screaming]

302
00:20:24,619 --> 00:20:29,082
[muffle yelping]

303
00:20:32,377 --> 00:20:33,795
[tense music playing]

304
00:20:42,512 --> 00:20:44,555
[Baek-jeong exhales]

305
00:21:29,726 --> 00:21:30,768
What is it?

306
00:21:32,186 --> 00:21:34,981
National Intelligence.
They're all over here.

307
00:21:36,316 --> 00:21:37,900
Oh, this is fucked.

308
00:21:38,943 --> 00:21:40,153
What are we gonna do now?

309
00:21:41,321 --> 00:21:43,406
President Im, we might not--

310
00:21:44,907 --> 00:21:47,035
-[wheezes]
-You shut your fucking mouth.

311
00:21:47,535 --> 00:21:49,412
You said you would do it. Huh?

312
00:21:50,121 --> 00:21:52,415
You fucking with me?
You gonna keep screwing around?

313
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:56,878
-[Baek-jeong exhales]
-You have to… get out of here now.

314
00:21:56,961 --> 00:21:58,087
[exhales]

315
00:21:58,588 --> 00:21:59,464
Just listen.

316
00:21:59,964 --> 00:22:01,966
One more mistake you make…

317
00:22:02,633 --> 00:22:04,969
and I'll kill your mom and dad, all right?

318
00:22:05,053 --> 00:22:06,179
Understand?

319
00:22:06,262 --> 00:22:07,722
-[choked] Yes.
-[Baek-jeong exhales]

320
00:22:07,805 --> 00:22:10,892
[electronic voice] The phone is
turned off. Your call has been forwarded.

321
00:22:10,975 --> 00:22:12,060
[music fades]

322
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:17,648
The phone is turned off.
Your call has been forwarded.

323
00:22:20,234 --> 00:22:22,362
-You gave me the right numbers?
-[Gun-woo] I did.

324
00:22:22,945 --> 00:22:25,490
They're from the phones
that Lee Man-bae used as burners.

325
00:22:26,199 --> 00:22:28,451
Du-yeong got them from Moon Dong-jo.

326
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:35,875
-[Woo-jin] Min-beom.
-Hmm?

327
00:22:36,459 --> 00:22:37,502
Could I…

328
00:22:39,962 --> 00:22:42,215
join and fight alongside Gun-woo?

329
00:22:44,258 --> 00:22:46,469
If you suggest a two-on-two match,

330
00:22:47,095 --> 00:22:49,972
In-beom may also step up to fight
and go into the ring.

331
00:22:51,015 --> 00:22:51,849
Then,

332
00:22:53,267 --> 00:22:55,812
while Gun-woo and I are fighting…

333
00:22:58,064 --> 00:22:59,482
you could get his mother.

334
00:22:59,565 --> 00:23:01,609
[gentle music playing]

335
00:23:04,529 --> 00:23:05,988
Please make this work

336
00:23:06,489 --> 00:23:07,824
to rescue his mom.

337
00:23:11,035 --> 00:23:12,036
I will.

338
00:23:13,037 --> 00:23:13,871
Of course.

339
00:23:15,331 --> 00:23:16,165
[Woo-jin] Thank you.

340
00:23:19,710 --> 00:23:21,295
[breathes deeply]

341
00:23:23,423 --> 00:23:24,465
[music fades]

342
00:23:24,549 --> 00:23:26,259
[outbound call ringing]

343
00:23:28,636 --> 00:23:31,264
[cell phone buzzing]

344
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,645
[cell phone buzzes]

345
00:23:38,271 --> 00:23:39,313
[sighs]

346
00:23:42,275 --> 00:23:43,276
[Min-beom] Lee Man-bae.

347
00:23:43,985 --> 00:23:45,111
Who is this?

348
00:23:45,194 --> 00:23:46,654
It's Hong Min-beom.

349
00:23:48,030 --> 00:23:49,740
Put Im Baek-jeong on the phone.

350
00:23:52,493 --> 00:23:53,911
Why would I bother?

351
00:23:54,745 --> 00:23:57,874
Your mom's in a nursing home
in Chuncheon, right, Lee Dong-hyeon?

352
00:23:59,208 --> 00:24:00,751
Don't think I won't hurt her.

353
00:24:00,835 --> 00:24:02,837
[tense music playing]

354
00:24:15,975 --> 00:24:18,895
President Im.
Hong Min-beom's on the phone.

355
00:24:22,315 --> 00:24:24,567
-Did you call that guy?
-No. I wouldn't.

356
00:24:30,448 --> 00:24:31,324
Speak.

357
00:24:32,325 --> 00:24:33,993
Let's have another matchup round.

358
00:24:35,786 --> 00:24:37,788
Gun-woo and Woo-jin against

359
00:24:38,456 --> 00:24:39,624
you and Kang In-beom.

360
00:24:39,707 --> 00:24:40,666
Why would I?

361
00:24:41,667 --> 00:24:45,838
We'll bet 100 billion won each.
The winner will take it all.

362
00:24:49,133 --> 00:24:49,967
[chuckles]

363
00:25:02,188 --> 00:25:05,483
[whimpers] Let go of me!

364
00:25:05,566 --> 00:25:08,444
[So-yeon screaming]

365
00:25:09,070 --> 00:25:11,322
Give me the phone. Give me that shit!

366
00:25:11,906 --> 00:25:13,074
[So-yeon] Let go!

367
00:25:13,157 --> 00:25:16,619
[So-yeon breathes shakily]

368
00:25:16,702 --> 00:25:19,747
100 billion won is gonna be exchanged
into Bitcoin and sent to me now,

369
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:22,291
or I'll cut off this lady's face
and send it over by courier.

370
00:25:22,375 --> 00:25:25,002
You stupid fuck. You can't push me around.

371
00:25:25,086 --> 00:25:27,296
-You think I'm weak or something? Huh?
-[So-yeon gasps]

372
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:30,174
Do you know why you're stuck in Korea?

373
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:33,928
The National Intelligence Service agents
are at the airport.

374
00:25:34,595 --> 00:25:37,640
My uncle's the director
of the National Intelligence Service.

375
00:25:37,723 --> 00:25:40,643
So, what, you want a fucking cookie?
Wire the funds.

376
00:25:40,726 --> 00:25:42,311
[So-yeon gasps]

377
00:25:42,395 --> 00:25:44,230
Or her face is gonna get fucked up.

378
00:25:45,815 --> 00:25:46,816
Kill her!

379
00:25:48,359 --> 00:25:50,903
Give me a reason to kill you.

380
00:25:51,404 --> 00:25:52,405
You'll regret that.

381
00:25:52,488 --> 00:25:55,074
Try me and see what'll happen, bastard.

382
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,326
[disconnection bleep]

383
00:26:01,080 --> 00:26:03,040
[So-yeon whimpers]

384
00:26:03,124 --> 00:26:05,209
[gasping]

385
00:26:05,293 --> 00:26:08,254
Yeah. They're stupid enough
to think I won't kill you.

386
00:26:08,337 --> 00:26:10,298
President Im, I'll fix this for you.

387
00:26:10,381 --> 00:26:11,549
You little shit.

388
00:26:11,632 --> 00:26:15,886
It's the National Intelligence Service.
We could get stuck in Korea forever.

389
00:26:15,970 --> 00:26:18,764
If we stay, it'll only take a while
until we're caught by the police.

390
00:26:18,848 --> 00:26:20,641
So, what are you gonna do?

391
00:26:20,725 --> 00:26:21,851
I…

392
00:26:23,019 --> 00:26:24,770
I'll get this figured out.

393
00:26:24,854 --> 00:26:27,064
I'll also look into going to Thailand.

394
00:26:27,148 --> 00:26:29,275
I need only a few more days.

395
00:26:29,775 --> 00:26:32,111
And I'll make sure this match goes ahead,

396
00:26:32,778 --> 00:26:34,905
and you won't put down any money.

397
00:26:34,989 --> 00:26:36,866
[tense music swells]

398
00:26:38,159 --> 00:26:39,118
[Baek-jeong sighs]

399
00:26:40,036 --> 00:26:41,370
Ah, shit.

400
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,539
You have ten days.

401
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:46,167
Get this sorted out in ten days.

402
00:26:47,084 --> 00:26:49,128
Or I'll be the one to kill you.

403
00:26:49,879 --> 00:26:51,672
Yes, I understand.

404
00:26:55,676 --> 00:26:56,636
[scissors clatter]

405
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:01,807
[music fades]

406
00:27:05,436 --> 00:27:06,395
[Woo-jin] Min-beom,

407
00:27:07,146 --> 00:27:09,440
what if they do something to Ms. Yoon?

408
00:27:09,940 --> 00:27:11,108
What do we do then?

409
00:27:13,027 --> 00:27:14,403
Let's wait a little longer.

410
00:27:21,452 --> 00:27:22,578
[exhales]

411
00:27:24,372 --> 00:27:27,458
[cell phone buzzing]

412
00:27:36,717 --> 00:27:40,346
[Man-bae] President Hong Min-beom,
please excuse me for this,

413
00:27:40,846 --> 00:27:42,348
but whether you meant to or not,

414
00:27:43,391 --> 00:27:45,726
if you get Im Baek-jeong
worked up like that,

415
00:27:47,061 --> 00:27:48,604
he'll do serious damage.

416
00:27:48,688 --> 00:27:49,897
He's a loose cannon.

417
00:27:49,980 --> 00:27:50,940
[tense music playing]

418
00:27:51,023 --> 00:27:54,485
Now, here's what I can do for you,
and I hope you'll accept it.

419
00:27:54,985 --> 00:27:56,195
Think it through.

420
00:27:56,696 --> 00:27:58,322
We won't put any money down.

421
00:27:58,406 --> 00:28:02,952
Instead, Kim Gun-woo's mom
will be escorted near the venue.

422
00:28:03,035 --> 00:28:06,080
If we lose, we'll release her.

423
00:28:06,163 --> 00:28:07,581
But if we win,

424
00:28:07,665 --> 00:28:09,458
we'll take the entire pot,

425
00:28:09,959 --> 00:28:13,045
and leave on the private jet
you have waiting for us you've prepped.

426
00:28:13,921 --> 00:28:17,425
Once we've safely arrived
at our destination, we'll release her.

427
00:28:17,508 --> 00:28:19,343
This is the best I can do,

428
00:28:19,427 --> 00:28:22,096
and a promise I'll make with my life,
so trust me.

429
00:28:22,179 --> 00:28:23,347
If there are any mix-ups,

430
00:28:24,598 --> 00:28:26,058
even by chance,

431
00:28:26,142 --> 00:28:29,186
and anything happens
that puts us in jeopardy,

432
00:28:29,270 --> 00:28:31,313
say, others get involved…

433
00:28:32,273 --> 00:28:34,650
You know I've got ears
inside the police, right?

434
00:28:35,151 --> 00:28:38,529
If I hear anything slightly off,
Kim Gun-woo won't see his mom again.

435
00:28:38,612 --> 00:28:41,157
She'll never be part of his life again.

436
00:28:42,199 --> 00:28:43,576
You understand?

437
00:28:44,326 --> 00:28:45,870
I trust that you do.

438
00:28:46,620 --> 00:28:50,166
So I'll contact you
two hours before the start of the match,

439
00:28:50,249 --> 00:28:51,500
which will be in two days.

440
00:28:51,584 --> 00:28:53,377
Send us your wager in Bitcoin.

441
00:28:53,461 --> 00:28:55,838
I'm turning off this phone
so it can't be tracked.

442
00:28:55,921 --> 00:28:58,507
-Did you understand all that?
-[Min-beom] Yes.

443
00:28:59,091 --> 00:29:00,760
I'll be back in touch.

444
00:29:06,807 --> 00:29:09,351
Until the match,
Ms. Yoon will stay secure.

445
00:29:11,562 --> 00:29:14,148
I'll outline a course of action.

446
00:29:15,024 --> 00:29:17,109
I can gather some men we can trust.

447
00:29:19,779 --> 00:29:23,073
Woo-jin and I
will come back much stronger.

448
00:29:27,244 --> 00:29:29,872
I also got us a private plane to Thailand.

449
00:29:32,708 --> 00:29:35,044
Fight Kim Gun-woo and Hong Woo-jin

450
00:29:35,544 --> 00:29:37,463
in a two-on-two match in ten days.

451
00:29:40,299 --> 00:29:42,009
I'll clash with Kim Gun-woo.

452
00:29:42,092 --> 00:29:43,052
[In-beom exhales]

453
00:29:47,223 --> 00:29:48,349
Kim Gun-woo

454
00:29:49,266 --> 00:29:50,309
is mine to kill.

455
00:29:56,482 --> 00:29:58,484
[somber music playing]

456
00:30:01,362 --> 00:30:03,030
[Woo-jin] Oh, it's right here.

457
00:30:03,113 --> 00:30:05,407
GUNSAN GYM

458
00:30:05,491 --> 00:30:09,203
-[coach] Jab, then cross. Again.
-[man] Coach, someone's here to see you.

459
00:30:15,501 --> 00:30:16,794
[Gun-woo and Woo-jin] Hello, sir.

460
00:30:21,006 --> 00:30:22,633
-Do your drills over there.
-[man] Yes.

461
00:30:33,185 --> 00:30:35,729
I guess you're Mr. Hong's son?

462
00:30:36,772 --> 00:30:37,606
Yes.

463
00:30:40,901 --> 00:30:41,944
Nice to meet you.

464
00:30:44,905 --> 00:30:46,365
Nice to meet you. I'm Kim Gun-woo.

465
00:30:51,328 --> 00:30:54,498
But you're the one
who fought Baek-jeong without gloves.

466
00:30:55,499 --> 00:30:56,625
Yes.

467
00:30:57,877 --> 00:30:58,794
[sighs]

468
00:31:01,297 --> 00:31:02,381
I'm Heo Cheong-ho.

469
00:31:04,091 --> 00:31:05,426
So, why have you come here?

470
00:31:06,427 --> 00:31:07,887
We're fighting Im Baek-jeong.

471
00:31:08,637 --> 00:31:10,431
Could you train us for the match?

472
00:31:11,015 --> 00:31:13,183
We'd appreciate it if you could help us.

473
00:31:17,354 --> 00:31:18,814
Are you looking for revenge?

474
00:31:19,732 --> 00:31:21,901
Im Baek-jeong is the one
who kidnapped my mother.

475
00:31:24,486 --> 00:31:25,487
[sighs] Hmm.

476
00:31:29,158 --> 00:31:30,117
[inhales]

477
00:31:30,784 --> 00:31:32,661
I don't know if I can be of any help,

478
00:31:34,246 --> 00:31:35,581
but I'll train you.

479
00:31:37,291 --> 00:31:38,709
I'll teach you what I know.

480
00:31:41,295 --> 00:31:42,713
-Thanks very much.
-Thanks very much.

481
00:31:44,131 --> 00:31:45,633
Baek-jeong is quick.

482
00:31:46,342 --> 00:31:48,344
He has a fast right hand
and a heavy left hand.

483
00:31:48,844 --> 00:31:51,764
When he's in a southpaw stance,
watch for his jab. Got it?

484
00:31:52,264 --> 00:31:54,975
He's similar to Thomas Hearns,
the Motor City Cobra.

485
00:31:55,809 --> 00:31:57,019
Thomas Hearns?

486
00:31:57,519 --> 00:31:58,354
No idea.

487
00:31:59,396 --> 00:32:01,815
Chopping style. Well, uh…

488
00:32:02,524 --> 00:32:03,651
Uh, never mind.

489
00:32:03,734 --> 00:32:05,736
[suspenseful music playing]

490
00:32:10,699 --> 00:32:12,117
Watch this. Call it a flicker jab.

491
00:32:12,826 --> 00:32:15,663
You can't tell if it's gonna land
on your body or on your face.

492
00:32:15,746 --> 00:32:18,415
It's surprising
because it comes in deep, quickly.

493
00:32:19,041 --> 00:32:21,293
This jab requires the fighter
to have long arms.

494
00:32:22,336 --> 00:32:24,922
The thing to know
is that his punches aren't that strong,

495
00:32:25,005 --> 00:32:27,591
so if you're tough,
take his punches and get in close.

496
00:32:28,842 --> 00:32:33,681
But also that's Baek-jeong's trap,
since he knows his strength.

497
00:32:34,264 --> 00:32:36,266
If you try to get in too close
while taking his jab,

498
00:32:36,350 --> 00:32:38,560
he might step back
and set up a quick hook like this.

499
00:32:41,438 --> 00:32:43,440
[sighs] Mm.

500
00:32:44,441 --> 00:32:46,860
[Cheong-ho] The real reason
why Baek-jeong's dangerous

501
00:32:46,944 --> 00:32:49,989
is he knows good fighters
use speed, power, and their mind.

502
00:32:50,489 --> 00:32:53,617
He reads his opponent's mind very fast
and downloads the info.

503
00:32:53,701 --> 00:32:56,829
Uh, how is it possible to learn that?

504
00:32:59,331 --> 00:33:01,291
Baek-jeong's home life wasn't good.

505
00:33:01,375 --> 00:33:03,836
In middle school,
he ran away and stayed on the streets.

506
00:33:03,919 --> 00:33:04,795
[somber music playing]

507
00:33:04,878 --> 00:33:06,922
His father was a violent drunk.

508
00:33:07,006 --> 00:33:09,091
His father got so drunk

509
00:33:09,717 --> 00:33:12,011
he beat his mother until she died.

510
00:33:12,094 --> 00:33:16,932
He had to read people in order to survive
and live such a rough life.

511
00:33:19,935 --> 00:33:21,186
Now, come at me.

512
00:33:21,270 --> 00:33:23,188
-Okay.
-I'll teach you how to block his punches.

513
00:33:23,689 --> 00:33:24,940
Throw some jabs.

514
00:33:29,486 --> 00:33:31,196
How's this? Huh?

515
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,073
-I can't use my lead hand.
-[Cheong-ho] Right.

516
00:33:33,157 --> 00:33:34,408
If this happens,

517
00:33:34,491 --> 00:33:38,454
Baek-jeong can't use his right hand
and will throw a straight left instead.

518
00:33:38,537 --> 00:33:40,164
-Got it?
-[Gun-woo] Mm.

519
00:33:40,247 --> 00:33:43,667
Now, try coming at me again.
Yeah. Harder. Go.

520
00:33:44,918 --> 00:33:48,005
Not that way.
Stop dodging by turning it over fast.

521
00:33:48,088 --> 00:33:49,673
Think what can be done here.

522
00:33:50,257 --> 00:33:51,341
A counter.

523
00:33:51,425 --> 00:33:52,968
That's it. A counter.

524
00:33:53,052 --> 00:33:55,721
-Always the way to turn things around.
-A counter.

525
00:33:56,346 --> 00:33:57,556
Now, come at me.

526
00:33:58,307 --> 00:33:59,349
More. Again.

527
00:34:03,395 --> 00:34:04,730
[exhales]

528
00:34:07,107 --> 00:34:08,192
Good, yeah.

529
00:34:09,443 --> 00:34:11,487
This is southpaw Baek-jeong's weapon,

530
00:34:12,321 --> 00:34:14,156
and yours to keep and fight him with.

531
00:34:15,240 --> 00:34:17,076
[tense electronic music playing]

532
00:34:17,159 --> 00:34:20,537
Baek-jeong's professional record
is 18 fights, 17 wins.

533
00:34:20,621 --> 00:34:23,624
Out of those 17 wins, 15 were KOs.

534
00:34:23,707 --> 00:34:26,168
Thirteen were when
he was in the orthodox stance.

535
00:34:26,794 --> 00:34:28,504
He likes his left foot forward.

536
00:34:31,298 --> 00:34:32,216
Oh!

537
00:34:33,258 --> 00:34:34,134
Watch out.

538
00:34:34,635 --> 00:34:37,054
This move is the one
to anticipate the most.

539
00:34:37,137 --> 00:34:39,640
Especially when Baek-jeong's
firmly like this.

540
00:34:39,723 --> 00:34:41,475
If he gets you on this side, it's over.

541
00:34:41,558 --> 00:34:44,103
How do I block
when he comes at me so fast?

542
00:34:46,730 --> 00:34:49,733
Step faster. Boxing is
about where your feet are.

543
00:34:49,817 --> 00:34:52,361
You just plant your feet
on the ground firmly,

544
00:34:52,986 --> 00:34:55,572
then push up
with all the power you've got,

545
00:34:55,656 --> 00:34:57,241
and then bam!

546
00:34:57,825 --> 00:35:01,995
Big guys are slower. That's why
you have to fight with your quick steps.

547
00:35:02,079 --> 00:35:03,747
If he turns, you turn with him.

548
00:35:05,666 --> 00:35:08,210
Like this. Yeah, that's it.
Then he won't get in.

549
00:35:09,336 --> 00:35:10,254
You got it.

550
00:35:10,337 --> 00:35:11,380
[music fades]

551
00:35:11,463 --> 00:35:13,924
I have very different ideas
from the director,

552
00:35:14,550 --> 00:35:17,177
and I'm not sure
who I can trust in the department.

553
00:35:17,761 --> 00:35:20,013
No one knows when Gang-yong will wake up.

554
00:35:20,514 --> 00:35:22,641
This isn't a job
to be done alone, Myeong-hwan.

555
00:35:23,767 --> 00:35:27,479
Woo-jeong, the Green Pine Club's perfect
for this kind of thing, so don't worry.

556
00:35:28,063 --> 00:35:29,857
I'll notify them.
They'll get themselves ready.

557
00:35:29,940 --> 00:35:31,692
[tense music playing]

558
00:35:31,775 --> 00:35:33,610
We'll gather together
and follow your lead.

559
00:35:34,611 --> 00:35:35,821
Thanks so much.

560
00:35:39,616 --> 00:35:40,826
[cell phone buzzes]

561
00:35:43,912 --> 00:35:44,746
BLOODHOUNDS: SEOUL

562
00:35:44,830 --> 00:35:46,248
GYEONGGI-DO
20 GUARDS IN 2 DAYS

563
00:35:46,331 --> 00:35:47,624
10 MIL UPFRONT, 15 MIL AFTER

564
00:35:58,427 --> 00:35:59,678
I'M IN

565
00:35:59,761 --> 00:36:02,639
When I searched the address
that Lee Man-bae gave Du-yeong,

566
00:36:02,723 --> 00:36:04,016
this is what came up.

567
00:36:04,099 --> 00:36:07,561
Originally, they were going to be
universities, but construction was halted.

568
00:36:07,644 --> 00:36:10,731
Inside the building
could easily be over 100 rooms.

569
00:36:10,814 --> 00:36:14,693
That might be why
they've chosen this place for the match.

570
00:36:14,776 --> 00:36:16,904
It's a good place to hide Ms. Yoon.

571
00:36:16,987 --> 00:36:19,239
They can have the match
in one of the three buildings,

572
00:36:19,323 --> 00:36:21,116
while also hiding Ms. Yoon.

573
00:36:21,200 --> 00:36:25,370
All three buildings are located on a hill
so they can see everything.

574
00:36:25,454 --> 00:36:28,790
And so that means our chances
of finding Ms. Yoon before is very low.

575
00:36:28,874 --> 00:36:31,960
It'll be extremely dangerous
to try rescuing her from the outside.

576
00:36:34,338 --> 00:36:35,547
That's where I'll go inside.

577
00:36:38,425 --> 00:36:40,469
Once Gun-woo and Woo-jin's match begins,

578
00:36:41,178 --> 00:36:42,221
I'll look for Ms. Yoon.

579
00:36:42,721 --> 00:36:44,973
Wouldn't it be too dangerous
for you to be alone?

580
00:36:45,057 --> 00:36:47,935
If I'm alone,
it's the safest way to rescue her.

581
00:36:48,435 --> 00:36:50,437
That's why I need to do this by myself.

582
00:36:50,520 --> 00:36:53,690
Those men won't be concerned about me.

583
00:36:53,774 --> 00:36:54,816
Most importantly,

584
00:36:56,235 --> 00:36:57,986
her safety is the priority.

585
00:37:03,033 --> 00:37:04,076
[chuckles softly]

586
00:37:10,123 --> 00:37:12,167
Are the Bitcoins set up, President Hong?

587
00:37:12,751 --> 00:37:13,669
Yes.

588
00:37:24,096 --> 00:37:26,473
Tae-yeong, why don't you
come along with us?

589
00:37:27,140 --> 00:37:30,477
The Green Pine Tree Club members
will all be waiting near the buildings.

590
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:32,896
-Once she's rescued, we'll go in.
-Yeah, sounds good.

591
00:37:33,897 --> 00:37:35,190
I'll be there too.

592
00:37:36,024 --> 00:37:39,361
I have to enter the password
for the transfer of the Bitcoin.

593
00:37:41,613 --> 00:37:42,864
Okay, everyone.

594
00:37:44,491 --> 00:37:45,325
Let's be strong.

595
00:37:49,246 --> 00:37:50,330
Fighting for her.

596
00:37:51,039 --> 00:37:53,250
One, two, three…

597
00:37:53,333 --> 00:37:54,418
[all] Let's do it!

598
00:37:55,085 --> 00:37:57,713
Give me the one. One. One. One. One.

599
00:37:57,796 --> 00:37:59,089
Go faster. Go. Go faster.

600
00:37:59,172 --> 00:38:01,883
-Go faster!
-[Gun-woo yells]

601
00:38:02,843 --> 00:38:05,178
[grunts]

602
00:38:07,014 --> 00:38:07,931
[In-beom grunts]

603
00:38:08,432 --> 00:38:10,225
[yells]

604
00:38:10,309 --> 00:38:11,184
[snarls]

605
00:38:11,768 --> 00:38:13,103
-[grunts]
-Another!

606
00:38:13,729 --> 00:38:15,188
-[grunts]
-Another!

607
00:38:15,772 --> 00:38:17,774
-[grunts]
-One more. You can do it!

608
00:38:17,858 --> 00:38:19,109
[strains]

609
00:38:19,192 --> 00:38:20,402
Yes! Go!

610
00:38:20,986 --> 00:38:21,862
[Gun-woo pants]

611
00:38:24,323 --> 00:38:25,615
You all right?

612
00:38:26,199 --> 00:38:27,200
Yeah.

613
00:38:27,284 --> 00:38:29,411
[both grunting]

614
00:38:41,757 --> 00:38:43,467
[both grunt]

615
00:38:48,347 --> 00:38:49,848
-Sixty-nine!
-[grunts]

616
00:38:51,141 --> 00:38:53,185
-[strains]
-Seventy! Thirty more. Be faster!

617
00:38:53,268 --> 00:38:54,895
-[grunts]
-Seventy-one!

618
00:38:55,729 --> 00:38:57,981
-[grunts]
-[Woo-jin] Seventy-two!

619
00:38:58,065 --> 00:38:58,940
[strains]

620
00:38:59,024 --> 00:39:01,234
[yells]

621
00:39:02,944 --> 00:39:05,113
[strains]

622
00:39:05,697 --> 00:39:07,282
Use your core. Use your core strength!

623
00:39:07,366 --> 00:39:09,159
[Gun-woo grunts]

624
00:39:10,118 --> 00:39:12,287
-[Woo-jin] Use your core! Your core!
-[Gun-woo strains]

625
00:39:12,871 --> 00:39:14,414
-[Woo-jin] Yes!
-[strains]

626
00:39:18,001 --> 00:39:19,586
All right, go. Let's go!

627
00:39:20,253 --> 00:39:23,256
That's good! Keep doing it. Okay!

628
00:39:40,524 --> 00:39:42,401
-You good?
-[Woo-jin] Yeah.

629
00:39:44,486 --> 00:39:45,570
[music fades]

630
00:39:45,654 --> 00:39:47,447
I've been thinking about this
since last night.

631
00:39:47,531 --> 00:39:49,032
Would Im Baek-jeong

632
00:39:50,075 --> 00:39:51,952
have thought I would be fighting him?

633
00:39:52,452 --> 00:39:53,703
Would he ever imagine that?

634
00:39:53,787 --> 00:39:56,998
-Uh-uh. I would never imagine that.
-[eerie music playing]

635
00:39:57,082 --> 00:39:58,166
-That's right.
-Hmm.

636
00:39:58,250 --> 00:40:00,585
He's probably preparing to maul you

637
00:40:00,669 --> 00:40:02,754
and will get thrown off
if I get in the ring.

638
00:40:02,838 --> 00:40:03,839
[Gun-woo] Mm-hmm.

639
00:40:05,006 --> 00:40:08,135
If I have to take 100 punches
from that bastard,

640
00:40:08,218 --> 00:40:10,762
I won't let it end
until one of his eyes is cooked.

641
00:40:11,346 --> 00:40:15,225
He'll lose his sense of distance,
and then I'll get the advantage.

642
00:40:16,309 --> 00:40:17,769
Are you gonna be okay, Woo-jin?

643
00:40:22,732 --> 00:40:24,234
This is what I've got to do.

644
00:40:26,111 --> 00:40:27,696
And what should we do with Kang In-beom?

645
00:40:29,781 --> 00:40:32,284
[sighs] That's a big concern.

646
00:40:32,951 --> 00:40:34,828
Yes, you might have to fight them both.

647
00:40:35,620 --> 00:40:36,538
[sighs]

648
00:40:37,038 --> 00:40:38,790
[somber music playing]

649
00:40:39,499 --> 00:40:40,500
Woo-jin.

650
00:40:42,085 --> 00:40:46,673
In the IKFC, they wrap metal things
on their knuckles before the fight.

651
00:40:46,756 --> 00:40:48,258
That's a weapon, isn't it?

652
00:40:50,635 --> 00:40:52,637
I didn't use them
in the fight the last time.

653
00:40:54,097 --> 00:40:55,557
I thought if I did,

654
00:40:56,766 --> 00:40:58,393
no one would consider me a champion.

655
00:40:59,561 --> 00:41:00,729
But now,

656
00:41:00,812 --> 00:41:02,731
I'm gonna wear them this time.

657
00:41:04,691 --> 00:41:06,276
I was wrong before.

658
00:41:08,111 --> 00:41:10,197
I believed I could protect people

659
00:41:11,156 --> 00:41:12,782
with a boxer's heart, but I can't.

660
00:41:14,326 --> 00:41:16,036
Mr. Moon said so the other day.

661
00:41:17,078 --> 00:41:18,497
The only way to grab a beast

662
00:41:18,997 --> 00:41:21,249
is to become a scarier beast
without mercy.

663
00:41:22,417 --> 00:41:24,586
Which means my heart is as tough as steel.

664
00:41:27,130 --> 00:41:28,882
My fists will become a knife

665
00:41:30,008 --> 00:41:32,010
once my heart is as tough as steel.

666
00:41:34,304 --> 00:41:37,098
It's how I can stand
and shield my loved ones.

667
00:41:40,519 --> 00:41:42,479
I need to make my heart as tough as steel.

668
00:41:45,982 --> 00:41:46,942
Ack.

669
00:41:48,485 --> 00:41:49,319
Ack!

670
00:41:49,819 --> 00:41:51,821
[tense electronic music playing]

671
00:42:06,836 --> 00:42:08,463
BLOODHOUNDS: IKFC 38

672
00:42:10,382 --> 00:42:11,716
OLD JINAM CAMPUS, 12 P.M.

673
00:42:12,884 --> 00:42:14,052
[cell phone chimes]

674
00:42:14,135 --> 00:42:14,970
DU-YEONG

675
00:43:14,696 --> 00:43:16,698
[tense music playing]

676
00:43:31,296 --> 00:43:33,298
[indistinct chatter]

677
00:43:40,055 --> 00:43:41,264
All right!

678
00:43:44,225 --> 00:43:46,686
Face me and listen for a moment, please.

679
00:43:46,770 --> 00:43:49,147
You all got a ticket
when you came in, right?

680
00:43:50,190 --> 00:43:53,818
Now, take your spot based on your number.

681
00:43:53,902 --> 00:43:57,864
Anyone who leaves their spot during
the match will be considered a traitor.

682
00:43:57,947 --> 00:44:01,034
Please send me a text message
or kill them yourself.

683
00:44:01,826 --> 00:44:03,620
There's an extra reward.

684
00:44:05,163 --> 00:44:06,498
Fifty million won.

685
00:44:07,540 --> 00:44:10,210
Whoa! So fucking awesome!

686
00:44:10,293 --> 00:44:14,172
-[man 1] Yeah!
-Good. All of us, let's do it!

687
00:44:14,673 --> 00:44:16,091
-Yeah!
-[cheering]

688
00:44:16,174 --> 00:44:17,759
-[chuckles]
-[man 2] Let's go!

689
00:44:17,842 --> 00:44:19,010
-[man 3] Yeah.
-[laughter]

690
00:44:19,094 --> 00:44:20,178
[man 4] Yeah!

691
00:44:37,362 --> 00:44:39,155
PRESIDENT HONG MIN-BEOM

692
00:44:42,534 --> 00:44:44,869
OLD JINAM CAMPUS, 15:00

693
00:44:48,206 --> 00:44:49,040
It's time.

694
00:45:00,260 --> 00:45:01,386
[laughter]

695
00:45:02,011 --> 00:45:04,848
[man] That 50 million won
is all mine, you bastards!

696
00:45:05,473 --> 00:45:06,891
[laughter]

697
00:45:22,866 --> 00:45:23,825
Fighters have arrived.

698
00:45:24,576 --> 00:45:25,452
Get ready.

699
00:45:30,832 --> 00:45:31,750
[exhales]

700
00:45:32,625 --> 00:45:33,710
[snarls]

701
00:45:42,260 --> 00:45:44,012
[tense music continues]

702
00:46:06,034 --> 00:46:07,285
I'm Lee Man-bae.

703
00:46:12,540 --> 00:46:13,875
Show me your wallet.

704
00:46:17,837 --> 00:46:18,922
[Min-boom sighs]

705
00:46:33,728 --> 00:46:35,396
[breathes shakily]

706
00:46:44,405 --> 00:46:45,615
[gasps]

707
00:46:45,698 --> 00:46:46,741
This is it.

708
00:46:47,242 --> 00:46:48,284
I'm going in.

709
00:47:40,128 --> 00:47:41,754
BLOODHOUNDS: IKFC 38

710
00:47:41,838 --> 00:47:43,047
[cell phone buzzes]

711
00:47:43,131 --> 00:47:46,718
THE FIGHT IS ON

712
00:47:46,801 --> 00:47:48,803
[suspenseful music playing]

713
00:47:53,433 --> 00:47:54,517
Hey,

714
00:47:55,727 --> 00:47:56,769
do you have a cigarette?

715
00:48:05,111 --> 00:48:06,154
And a light?

716
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:12,285
-[knife slices]
-[groans]

717
00:48:12,911 --> 00:48:13,912
[knife slices]

718
00:48:23,212 --> 00:48:25,214
[ominous music playing]

719
00:48:38,269 --> 00:48:40,355
What the fuck are you doing here?

720
00:48:40,438 --> 00:48:41,898
What the fuck do you think?

721
00:48:42,398 --> 00:48:45,276
Today, it's you and me, Baek-jeong,

722
00:48:45,360 --> 00:48:47,195
you fucking asshole fuckface.

723
00:48:47,987 --> 00:48:48,863
You're gonna die.

724
00:48:49,447 --> 00:48:50,365
"You're gonna die."

725
00:48:52,325 --> 00:48:53,159
You scared?

726
00:48:53,242 --> 00:48:54,243
[laughs]

727
00:48:54,744 --> 00:48:55,995
Scared?

728
00:48:56,579 --> 00:48:58,456
Scared? Huh, scared?

729
00:48:58,539 --> 00:49:00,500
[dramatic music playing]

730
00:49:11,219 --> 00:49:13,012
You motherfucker! [grunts]

731
00:49:19,519 --> 00:49:21,145
[groans]

732
00:49:21,229 --> 00:49:23,564
Who the hell
do you think you are? Get out!

733
00:49:24,649 --> 00:49:25,692
[Woo-jin groans]

734
00:49:31,781 --> 00:49:33,032
Scared?

735
00:49:33,116 --> 00:49:34,617
Scared? Huh?

736
00:49:45,253 --> 00:49:47,463
-[tense music playing]
-[Woo-jin groans]

737
00:49:47,547 --> 00:49:48,464
[Woo-jin coughs]

738
00:49:48,965 --> 00:49:50,133
[Woo-jin groans]

739
00:50:02,562 --> 00:50:03,646
Hmm?

740
00:50:04,981 --> 00:50:06,649
-[man 1 yells]
-[knife flies through air]

741
00:50:08,151 --> 00:50:09,485
-[grunts]
-[man 2] Oh, fuck.

742
00:50:09,569 --> 00:50:11,696
-[knife clatters]
-I fucking love this!

743
00:50:12,530 --> 00:50:15,116
-[knives fly through air]
-[yells] Hya!

744
00:50:17,577 --> 00:50:19,454
-[groans]
-[man 1] Where you going?

745
00:50:19,537 --> 00:50:20,997
-[man 1 yells]
-[Du-yeong grunts]

746
00:50:23,666 --> 00:50:24,584
Shitface!

747
00:50:29,839 --> 00:50:31,758
Fuck around and find out, dumbass.

748
00:50:33,342 --> 00:50:34,594
Scared?

749
00:50:36,512 --> 00:50:37,638
Baek-jeong, scared?

750
00:50:48,858 --> 00:50:50,193
Ah, fuck you!

751
00:50:51,694 --> 00:50:52,695
[grunts]

752
00:50:54,864 --> 00:50:57,617
You want this asshole to die?
Enter the ring!

753
00:50:57,700 --> 00:50:58,785
[music fades]

754
00:50:59,327 --> 00:51:00,828
[Woo-jin groans]

755
00:51:01,662 --> 00:51:05,166
[groans]

756
00:51:05,249 --> 00:51:06,959
[determined music playing]

757
00:51:10,463 --> 00:51:11,297
Scared?

758
00:51:14,675 --> 00:51:16,427
[bellows] Scared?!

759
00:51:16,511 --> 00:51:18,137
[Baek-jeong yells]

760
00:51:19,597 --> 00:51:21,057
[yells]

761
00:51:22,725 --> 00:51:23,726
[yells]

762
00:51:23,810 --> 00:51:25,812
[dramatic music playing]

763
00:51:27,605 --> 00:51:29,607
[panting]

764
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:32,860
Ah, shit.

765
00:51:36,989 --> 00:51:38,074
Stop the bleeding.

766
00:51:42,120 --> 00:51:44,205
Stupid little bastard.

767
00:51:45,790 --> 00:51:48,084
If the blood doesn't stop, I'll kill you.

768
00:51:48,167 --> 00:51:49,127
[man] Understood.

769
00:51:49,710 --> 00:51:50,545
[exhales]

770
00:51:51,504 --> 00:51:53,297
[somber music playing]

771
00:51:53,381 --> 00:51:55,049
[breathes shakily]

772
00:51:55,133 --> 00:51:56,717
I got his eye.

773
00:51:57,844 --> 00:52:00,346
Mm-hmm. You did.

774
00:52:05,601 --> 00:52:07,228
[breathes heavily]

775
00:52:08,187 --> 00:52:09,480
I'll finish this fight.

776
00:52:11,065 --> 00:52:11,983
[Woo-jin] Mm.

777
00:52:15,069 --> 00:52:16,028
[Gun-woo] Mm.

778
00:52:19,949 --> 00:52:21,909
-[man 1 grunts]
-[knife slices]

